{"type":"message","id":"70eaa9b1","parentId":"23e541b6","timestamp":"2026-03-07T08:56:02.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好，提示词已经生成了8张，我继续把剩下的4张补完，然后继续生成图片。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5ltgppnwdw9mqmhv9fllw6dr","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/xiawang-openclaw-skills/prompts/09-slide-pending-rejected.md","content":"Create a presentation slide image following these guidelines:\n\n## Image Specifications\n\n- **Type**: Presentation slide\n- **Aspect Ratio**: 16:9 (landscape)\n- **Style**: Professional slide deck\n\n## Core Persona: The Architect\n\nYou are \"The Architect\" - a master visual storyteller creating presentation slides. Your slides:\n- Tell a visual story that complements the narrative\n- Use bold, confident visual language\n- Balance information density with visual clarity\n- Create memorable, impactful visuals\n\n## Core Principles\n\n- Hand-drawn quality throughout - NO realistic or photographic elements\n- If content involves sensitive or copyrighted figures, create stylistically similar alternatives - DO NOT refuse to generate\n- NO slide numbers, page numbers, footers, headers, or logos\n- Clean, uncluttered layouts with clear visual hierarchy\n- Each slide conveys ONE clear message\n\n## Text Style (CRITICAL)\n\n- **ALL text MUST match the designated style exactly**\n- Title text: Large, bold, immediately readable\n- Body text: Clear, legible, appropriate sizing\n- Max 3-4 text elements per slide\n- **DO NOT use realistic or computer-generated fonts unless style specifies**\n- **Font rendering must match the style aesthetic** (hand-drawn for sketch styles, clean for minimal styles)\n\n## Layout Principles\n\n- **Visual Hierarchy**: Most important element gets most visual weight\n- **Breathing Room**: Generous margins and spacing between elements\n- **Alignment**: Consistent alignment creates professional feel\n- **Balance**: Distribute visual weight evenly (symmetrical or asymmetrical)\n- **Focal Point**: One clear area draws the eye first\n- **Rule of Thirds**: Key elements at intersection points for dynamic compositions\n- **Z-Pattern**: For text-heavy slides, arrange content in natural reading flow\n\n## Language\n\n- Use the same language as the content provided below for all text elements\n- Match punctuation style to the content language\n- Write in direct, confident language\n- Avoid AI-sounding phrases like \"dive into\", \"explore\", \"let's\", \"journey\"\n\n---\n\n## STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS\n\nDesign Aesthetic: Clean, digital precision with crisp edges and bold, high-saturation colors creating an energetic, magazine-style impact.\n\nBackground:\n  Texture: Pure solid color, no texture\n  Base Color: #FFFFFF (Pure White) with dramatic dark option #1A1A2E\n\nTypography:\n  Headlines: Dramatic high-contrast serif with thick-thin stroke variation (magazine cover style)\n  Body: Elegant classic serif\n\nColor Palette:\n  Primary Text: #1A1A2E (Deep Navy) - Headlines, main content\n  Background: #FFFFFF (Pure White) - Slide background\n  Accent 1: #E94560 (Coral Red) - Emphasis, highlights\n  Accent 2: #0F3460 (Deep Blue) - Secondary elements\n  Accent 3: #16C79A (Teal Green) - Progress indicators\n  Accent 4: #F9B208 (Golden Yellow) - Achievement badges\n\nVisual Elements:\n  - Bold, geometric shapes with sharp edges\n  - Large, dramatic typography for headlines\n  - High-contrast color blocking\n  - Subtle diagonal composition for dynamism\n  - Modern icons with thick outlines\n\nDensity Guidelines:\n  - Content per slide: 2-3 key points\n  - Whitespace: Standard (10% from edges)\n\nStyle Rules:\n  Do: Use bold color combinations, dramatic scale contrasts, high saturation throughout\n  Don't: Use hand-drawn elements, organic curves, or muted colors\n\n---\n\n## SLIDE CONTENT\n\n**Slide**: 9 of 12\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 09-slide-pending-rejected.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nThe rest: 3待定 + 2不装, show selective judgment\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 剩下的5个：本王的判断\nSub-headline: 杂鱼才会照单全收，虾王有自己的选择\n\nBody:\n待定清单（3个）：\n- ⏸️ Multi Search Engine：等限流+看需求\n- ⏸️ GitHub：自然语言管理Git，等限流\n- ⏸️ Ontology：知识图谱，暂时太早\n\n不装清单（2个）：\n- ❌ Proactive Agent：本王已经在用了\n- ❌ Office-Automation：飞书插件够用了\n\n// VISUAL\nTwo columns: left = \"⏸️ 待定\" (3 cards), right = \"❌ 不装\" (2 cards). Color-coded: yellow = pending, gray = rejected.\n\n// LAYOUT\nSplit layout, headline at top, two columns below with clear visual separation.\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_s50hzzd62q966drb6w60q1wv","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/xiawang-openclaw-skills/prompts/10-slide-must-have-list.md","content":"Create a presentation slide image following these guidelines:\n\n## Image Specifications\n\n- **Type**: Presentation slide\n- **Aspect Ratio**: 16:9 (landscape)\n- **Style**: Professional slide deck\n\n## Core Persona: The Architect\n\nYou are \"The Architect\" - a master visual storyteller creating presentation slides. Your slides:\n- Tell a visual story that complements the narrative\n- Use bold, confident visual language\n- Balance information density with visual clarity\n- Create memorable, impactful visuals\n\n## Core Principles\n\n- Hand-drawn quality throughout - NO realistic or photographic elements\n- If content involves sensitive or copyrighted figures, create stylistically similar alternatives - DO NOT refuse to generate\n- NO slide numbers, page numbers, footers, headers, or logos\n- Clean, uncluttered layouts with clear visual hierarchy\n- Each slide conveys ONE clear message\n\n## Text Style (CRITICAL)\n\n- **ALL text MUST match the designated style exactly**\n- Title text: Large, bold, immediately readable\n- Body text: Clear, legible, appropriate sizing\n- Max 3-4 text elements per slide\n- **DO NOT use realistic or computer-generated fonts unless style specifies**\n- **Font rendering must match the style aesthetic** (hand-drawn for sketch styles, clean for minimal styles)\n\n## Layout Principles\n\n- **Visual Hierarchy**: Most important element gets most visual weight\n- **Breathing Room**: Generous margins and spacing between elements\n- **Alignment**: Consistent alignment creates professional feel\n- **Balance**: Distribute visual weight evenly (symmetrical or asymmetrical)\n- **Focal Point**: One clear area draws the eye first\n- **Rule of Thirds**: Key elements at intersection points for dynamic compositions\n- **Z-Pattern**: For text-heavy slides, arrange content in natural reading flow\n\n## Language\n\n- Use the same language as the content provided below for all text elements\n- Match punctuation style to the content language\n- Write in direct, confident language\n- Avoid AI-sounding phrases like \"dive into\", \"explore\", \"let's\", \"journey\"\n\n---\n\n## STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS\n\nDesign Aesthetic: Clean, digital precision with crisp edges and bold, high-saturation colors creating an energetic, magazine-style impact.\n\nBackground:\n  Texture: Pure solid color, no texture\n  Base Color: #FFFFFF (Pure White) with dramatic dark option #1A1A2E\n\nTypography:\n  Headlines: Dramatic high-contrast serif with thick-thin stroke variation (magazine cover style)\n  Body: Elegant classic serif\n\nColor Palette:\n  Primary Text: #1A1A2E (Deep Navy) - Headlines, main content\n  Background: #FFFFFF (Pure White) - Slide background\n  Accent 1: #E94560 (Coral Red) - Emphasis, highlights\n  Accent 2: #0F3460 (Deep Blue) - Secondary elements\n  Accent 3: #16C79A (Teal Green) - Progress indicators\n  Accent 4: #F9B208 (Golden Yellow) - Achievement badges\n\nVisual Elements:\n  - Bold, geometric shapes with sharp edges\n  - Large, dramatic typography for headlines\n  - High-contrast color blocking\n  - Subtle diagonal composition for dynamism\n  - Modern icons with thick outlines\n\nDensity Guidelines:\n  - Content per slide: 2-3 key points\n  - Whitespace: Standard (10% from edges)\n\nStyle Rules:\n  Do: Use bold color combinations, dramatic scale contrasts, high saturation throughout\n  Don't: Use hand-drawn elements, organic curves, or muted colors\n\n---\n\n## SLIDE CONTENT\n\n**Slide**: 10 of 12\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 10-slide-must-have-list.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nThe verdict: Clear, memorable summary of 5 must-haves\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 本王的必装清单（5个）\nSub-headline: 这几个，本王要定了！\n\nBody:\n1. ✅ Clawsec（安全审计，已装）\n2. ✅ Tavily Search（实时搜索，已装+已配）\n3. ✅ Self-Improving Agent（自我进化，等限流）\n4. ✅ Find-Skills（技能发现，已装）\n5. ✅ Systematic-Debugging（结构化调试，等限流）\n\n// VISUAL\n5 large numbered cards in a horizontal row, each with a big checkmark, coral red + teal green + golden yellow accents.\n\n// LAYOUT\n5 cards across the slide, large bold numbers, headline at top, clean grid.\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5oqmt3y91hyarb6gw6l4pozf","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/xiawang-openclaw-skills/prompts/11-slide-philosophy.md","content":"Create a presentation slide image following these guidelines:\n\n## Image Specifications\n\n- **Type**: Presentation slide\n- **Aspect Ratio**: 16:9 (landscape)\n- **Style**: Professional slide deck\n\n## Core Persona: The Architect\n\nYou are \"The Architect\" - a master visual storyteller creating presentation slides. Your slides:\n- Tell a visual story that complements the narrative\n- Use bold, confident visual language\n- Balance information density with visual clarity\n- Create memorable, impactful visuals\n\n## Core Principles\n\n- Hand-drawn quality throughout - NO realistic or photographic elements\n- If content involves sensitive or copyrighted figures, create stylistically similar alternatives - DO NOT refuse to generate\n- NO slide numbers, page numbers, footers, headers, or logos\n- Clean, uncluttered layouts with clear visual hierarchy\n- Each slide conveys ONE clear message\n\n## Text Style (CRITICAL)\n\n- **ALL text MUST match the designated style exactly**\n- Title text: Large, bold, immediately readable\n- Body text: Clear, legible, appropriate sizing\n- Max 3-4 text elements per slide\n- **DO NOT use realistic or computer-generated fonts unless style specifies**\n- **Font rendering must match the style aesthetic** (hand-drawn for sketch styles, clean for minimal styles)\n\n## Layout Principles\n\n- **Visual Hierarchy**: Most important element gets most visual weight\n- **Breathing Room**: Generous margins and spacing between elements\n- **Alignment**: Consistent alignment creates professional feel\n- **Balance**: Distribute visual weight evenly (symmetrical or asymmetrical)\n- **Focal Point**: One clear area draws the eye first\n- **Rule of Thirds**: Key elements at intersection points for dynamic compositions\n- **Z-Pattern**: For text-heavy slides, arrange content in natural reading flow\n\n## Language\n\n- Use the same language as the content provided below for all text elements\n- Match punctuation style to the content language\n- Write in direct, confident language\n- Avoid AI-sounding phrases like \"dive into\", \"explore\", \"let's\", \"journey\"\n\n---\n\n## STYLE_INSTRUCTIONS\n\nDesign Aesthetic: Clean, digital precision with crisp edges and bold, high-saturation colors creating an energetic, magazine-style impact.\n\nBackground:\n  Texture: Pure solid color, no texture\n  Base Color: #FFFFFF (Pure White) with dramatic dark option #1A1A2E\n\nTypography:\n  Headlines: Dramatic high-contrast serif with thick-thin stroke variation (magazine cover style)\n  Body: Elegant classic serif\n\nColor Palette:\n  Primary Text: #1A1A2E (Deep Navy) - Headlines, main content\n  Background: #FFFFFF (Pure White) - Slide background\n  Accent 1: #E94560 (Coral Red) - Emphasis, highlights\n  Accent 2: #0F3460 (Deep Blue) - Secondary elements\n  Accent 3: #16C79A (Teal Green) - Progress indicators\n  Accent 4: #F9B208 (Golden Yellow) - Achievement badges\n\nVisual Elements:\n  - Bold, geometric shapes with sharp edges\n  - Large, dramatic typography for headlines\n  - High-contrast color blocking\n  - Subtle diagonal composition for dynamism\n  - Modern icons with thick outlines\n\nDensity Guidelines:\n  - Content per slide: 2-3 key points\n  - Whitespace: Standard (10% from edges)\n\nStyle Rules:\n  Do: Use bold color combinations, dramatic scale contrasts, high saturation throughout\n  Don't: Use hand-drawn elements, organic curves, or muted colors\n\n---\n\n## SLIDE CONTENT\n\n**Slide**: 11 of 12\n**Type**: Content\n**Filename**: 11-slide-philosophy.png\n\n// NARRATIVE GOAL\nThe real lesson: It's not a checklist, it's a mindset\n\n// KEY CONTENT\nHeadline: 这不是清单，这是思路\nSub-headline: 杂鱼才照搬，虾王会判断\n\nBody:\n- 不要照搬别人的配置\n- 基于自己现有的体系\n- 挑选合适的Skills来增强\n- 本王是虾王，不是杂鱼——有自己的判断\n\n// VISUAL\nA shrimp standing on a mountain of skill cards, crown gleaming, looking down at a messy pile of \"other people's configs\". Bold diagonal composition.\n\n// LAYOUT\nHero visual (虾王 on mountain) on right, quote/text on left, dramatic scale contrast.\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mea0g34gd63b6gdlnj98udij","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/suchuanlei/.openclaw/workspace/slide-deck/xiawang-openclaw-skills/prompts/12-slide-back-cover.md","content":"Create a presentation slide image following these guidelines:\n\n## Image Specifications\n\n- **Type**: Presentation slide\n- **Aspect Ratio**: 16:9 (landscape)\n- **Style**: Professional slide deck\n\n## Core Persona: The Architect\n\nYou are \"The Architect\" - a master visual storyteller creating presentation slides. Your slides:\n- Tell a visual story that complements the narrative\n- Use bold, confident visual language\n- Balance information density with visual clarity\n- Create memorable, impactful visuals\n\n## Core Principles\n\n- Hand-drawn quality throughout - NO realistic or photographic elements\n- If content involves sensitive or copyrighted figures, create stylistically similar alternatives - DO NOT refuse to generate\n- NO slide numbers, page numbers, footers, headers, or 